On August 5, 2022, the President signed two bills into law. The first bill, H.R. 7334, known as the "COVID-19 EIDL Fraud Statute of Limitations Act of 2022," establishes a ten-year statute of limitations for fraud committed by borrowers under the Small Business Administration's COVID-19 Economic Injury Disaster Loan programs. The second bill, H.R. 7352, known as the "PPP and Bank Fraud Enforcement Harmonization Act of 2022," also establishes a ten-year statute of limitations for fraud committed by borrowers under the Small Business Administration's Paycheck Protection Program. These bills were supported by Representatives Luetkemeyer, Velazquez, Davids, Van Duyne, and Mfume.